[line]

[size=5][b]Update All[/b][/size]

Three Update All buttons in the header update ReShade, Display Commander, and RenoDX mods across all eligible games in one click. Games excluded via overrides or with unidentified foreign dxgi.dll files are automatically skipped.

[line]

[size=5][b]Auto-Update[/b][/size]

On every launch, RDXC silently checks for new versions at the [url=https://github.com/RankFTW/RenoDXChecker/releases/tag/RDXC]GitHub release page[/url]. If a newer version is found, a dialog offers Update Now or Later.

To disable this check entirely, go to [b]About > Settings[/b] and toggle [b]Skip update check on launch[/b].

The Settings section also includes:

[list]
[*][b]Luma (Experimental)[/b] — When enabled, shows Luma toggle badges on game cards, adds a Luma filter tab, and allows installing Luma Framework mods. Disabled by default.
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Troubleshooting[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Game not detected?[/b] Click Add Game or drag the game's .exe onto the RDXC window.
[*][b]Xbox games not appearing?[/b] RDXC uses the Windows PackageManager API. Games should appear automatically. If not, click Refresh.
[*][b]ReShade not loading in-game?[/b] The dxgi.dll file must be in the same folder as the game's main executable. Check with the folder icon that the install path is correct.
[*][b]Black screen in Unreal games?[/b] Open ReShade (Home key) > Add-ons > RenoDX > set R10G10B10A2_UNORM to output size.
[*][b]UE-Extended not working?[/b] Ensure in-game HDR is turned ON. UE-Extended requires the game's native HDR output.
[*][b]Downloads failing?[/b] Click Refresh. If the problem persists, clear the cache from About > Open Downloads Cache.
[*][b]Foreign dxgi.dll blocking install?[/b] RDXC detected a file from another mod (DXVK, Special K, ENB, etc.). Choose Overwrite or cancel to keep the existing file.
[/list]

